data.meta_description:
890 likes, 2 comments - smithsoniannpg on May 20, 2024: "Happy Birthday to Cher, born in El Centro, California #OnThisDay in 1946. 🎤 🎉 

In 1965, Cher dropped her first big pop hit with husband Salvatore “Sonny” Bono, “I Got You Babe.” It sold over three million copies.

Alongside her booming musical career, Cher established herself as an actress. She starred in and won awards for numerous films, including “Silkwood” (1983) and “Moonstruck” (1987). Since arriving in Los Angeles in 1964, Cher has left her mark on pop culture and continues to inspire the next generation of performers.

📸: “Cher” by Francesco Scavullo, 1974 (printed 2004). National Portrait Gallery, Smithsonian Institution. Gift of The Motion Picture Group, Inc., Philadelphia, PA USA
